## Anti-Patterns (project-specific)

| Don't | Why / Do instead |
|-------|------------------|
| Assume JWT/`[Authorize]` | Package installed; `Program.cs` has no `UseAuthentication()` |
| Assume FluentValidation on Category | Pipeline registered; Category validates inline in handlers |
| Register/use `LoggingBehavior` | File exists; not in DI |
| Use `Error` record | Unused; handlers use `Result.Failure(string)` |
| Add repository/service layer | Handlers inject `AppDbContext` directly |
| Throw for business errors | `Result.Failure("â€¦ not found")` |
| Edit `AppDbContext.cs` | Scaffold only; use `AppDbContext.Partial.cs` |
| Create EF migrations | Schema via SQL + `DATABASE.md` |
| Extract shared DTOs early | Duplicate like Category until 3+ features need it |
| Use `DateTime.UtcNow` | Project uses `DateTime.Now` + legacy Npgsql switch |
| Query `Attribute` entity | DbContext alias: `AttributeEntity` |
| Build frontend before backend feature | No `frontend/` yet; API first |
| Duplicate slug/delete logic in UI | Backend owns business rules |
